04/05/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu has issued a decree appointing Gjergj Sauli as the new chairman of the Constitutional Court, succeeding Fehmi Abdiu.
Sauli has been a member of the Court since 2001.
By law, the judges are changed every three years, while the chairman is elected to a three-year term.
In other news, Public Order Minister Igli Toska voiced dissatisfaction Monday (3 May) with police training and efficiency He says only 5 per cent of the 8,000-strong police force has concrete field activity while the rest deal with statistics and desk duty.
(Albanian News - 04/05/04)
